cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.DC, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the security and reliability of cryptographic protocols, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). It also involves information theory (cs.IT) in terms of the randomness and unpredictability of the beacon outputs. The use of XORing multiple beacons together suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and possibly parallel computing (cs.CC). Finally, the mention of time sharing as a strategy for enhancing trustworthiness suggests a potential connection to distributed systems (cs.DS).
